<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-787] Simple Consumer connecting to Broker that is not the Leader generates wrong error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-787</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;0.8.0 HEAD from 3/4/2013&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using a SimpleConsumer, connect to a Broker that is NOT the leader for the topic/partition you want to fetch, but IS a replica.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On fetch the error returned is &apos;5&apos; &apos;ErrorMapping.LeaderNotAvailableCode&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Per email thread with Neha:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Ideally, you should get back  ErrorMapping.NotLeaderForPartitionCode&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Key part of the test is the Broker must be a replica. If the topic/partition is not on the Broker you get a different (correct) error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
